This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category as it deals with recommendation systems, which are a common application of IR techniques. The paper also proposes a novel method for learning interaction-based item embeddings, which involves machine learning and could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper mentions natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as word embeddings, which could place it in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) category. The paper also involves evaluating the proposed method in an industry-scale recommendation system, which could fall under the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) categories.
